{
  "stem": "1858.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 291.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, like this it went on for several hours.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then he gathered us together-- the seven of us-- and brought us back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why he did it?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For his amusement again, which many times things were done to us by the Nazis for their amusement.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what did they do to us?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Can you imagine?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I look back and I saw my sister standing and I was being led away, I never thought that time that I will see them again.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was again things to instill fear in us, and to terrorize us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these things were done to us by what we call human beings.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I wonder until today, how does a man do that to another human being?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "How does a soldier pick up an infant, toss him in the air, use him as a target practice, come home and pick up his own child and not feel any pain and regrets?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I know that this concentration camp life in the ghetto has affected me in such a terrible way that I thought that I will never recover from it, that i will never be a normal human being.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Being exposed to so much brutality, being exposed to such a hunger, how could I ever turn the clock back and become a decent human being?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When we were working in the field, it was a terrible time because many girls froze, became very ill.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we-- of course, we're being starved to death.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some girls that were planting potatoes started eating them and became very, very ill.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On May 8, unknown to us, the war has officially ended.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, that night, we went to sleep as usually, not knowing that we were being freed.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
